

license: OFL
category: serif
subsets: menu,latin,latin-ext

family: Quattrocento

designer: Pablo Impallari

approved: true
description: <p>The Quattrocento Roman typeface is \
  a Classic, Elegant, Sober and Strong typeface.</p> \
  <p>Their wide and open letterforms, and the great \
  x-height, make it very legible for body text at \
  small sizes. And their tiny details that only \
  shows up at bigger sizes make it also great \
  for display use.</p> \
  <p>Some of their distinctive characteristics \
  are:</p> \
  <ul> \
  <li>Low Contrast. The thins are just a \
  tad thiner than the thicks, almost monotone.</li> \
  <li>Cupped, tapered stems that flows naturally \
  into the serifs.</li> \
  <li>Distinctive K, R and & tail.</li> \
  <li>Cupped B, D, E, F, P, Q, R and T.</li> \
  <li>The Q is a humble expression of admiration \
  and gratitude for Doyald Young.</li> \
  <li>Alternate M, Two W alternates .</li> \
  <li>Narrow L, T for better fit.</li> \
  <li>Almost flat top serif on the lowercases.</li> \
  <li>Shoulders of the m and n rise above \
  the serif.</li> \
  <li>Serif-less bottom j and y.</li> \
  </ul>

font.Quattrocento-Regular.ttf.style: normal
font.Quattrocento-Bold.ttf.style: normal

font.Quattrocento-Regular.ttf.weight: 400
font.Quattrocento-Bold.ttf.weight: 700

